content.description: Left angling thin hands for 12' to straight up hands to the anchors.  Beautiful clean line in good rock, with a bit of softness toward the top.  Not technical or cruxy, but alot of continuous jamming.  Crackers be warned...
content.protection: .75, 1, 3x2, 3 Camalots.  Anchor is two newer bolts, with a single rap oval on decent slings.
content.location: Left side of the Basketball Wall, the obvious hand-size splitter left of the harder and longer "Foul Line".  Anchors visible from below.

content.description: Awesome fingers to hands; straight in, straight up. Maybe the best slitter of it's grade at the reef!
content.protection: .5, .75, 2x1, 3x2 Camalots.  Slung anchors visible from below.
content.location: Right side of the B-ball Wall, near a few other anchorless lines.

content.description: Hand jam in a right facing corner. Like the other routes on the wall "it's all in the crack".
content.protection: Hand size pro, that's #2 and #3 BD cams. Fixed anchors at the top.
content.location: The left splitter on the wall.
